{{wikipediapar|Alternativism}}
==English==

===Noun===
'''Alternativism''' (also [[alternativism]])
# {{philosophy}} An [[ideology#Adjective|ideology]] of limitless alternatives, and/or the practice of relating every [[logical]] alternative to a [[larger]] [[truth]].
# {{theology}} The belief that absolute truth must explain every [[legitimate]] alternative.

====Usage notes====
While this may seem like a [[protologism]] the word '''Alternativism''' has been implied, if not used, for decades now. The term itself is merely a [[canopy word]] meant to cover the [[variety]] of applications for different [[w:Alternative|Alternatives]]. It's most common [[usage]] or [[acceptance]] is in the [[context]] of specific [[alternative]] [[practices]]. An early [[endorsement]] of the term arose from analyzing alternative [[medicine]] movements. [http://www.csicop.org/si/9509/alternativism.html]

